{"name": "fastapi-storage-helper", "metadata": {"name": "fastapi-storage-helper", "version": "0.0.10", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["boto3", "boto", "botocore"], "summary": "FastAPI Storage Helper", "upload_time": 1732449953}, "documentation": ["# FastAPI Storage\n\n## Introduction\n\nFastAPI Storage provides helper functions for interacting with AWS S3, making it easier to handle file storage, presigned URLs, metadata, and content-type modifications\n\n### How to use\n\n#### Configuration\n\nFirst, configure the storage service by setting up AWS credentials and bucket information:\n\n```python\n# config/storage.py\nfrom fastapi_storage_helper import StorageService\nfrom config.setting import env\n\nstorage_service = StorageService(\n  access_key_id=env.AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID,\n  secret_key=env.AWS_SECRET_KEY,\n  region_name=env.AWS_REGION,\n  bucket=env.AWS_S3_BUCKET_NAME,\n)\n```\n\n#### Create Read Presign URL\n\nTo generate a presigned URL for reading a file from S3:\n\n```python\nfrom config.storage import storage_service\n\ndef get_media_url(self, s3_image_path: str):\n    return storage_service.create_read_presign_url(s3_image_path)\n```\n\n#### Create an Upload Presign URL\n\nTo generate a presigned URL for uploading a file to S3:\n\n```python\nfrom config.storage import storage_service\ndef get_upload_media_url(self, s3_image_path: str):\n    return storage_service.create_upload_presign_url(s3_image_path)\n```\n\n#### Upload file to S3\n\nTo directly upload a file to an S3 bucket:\n\n```python\nfrom config.storage import storage_service\n\ndef upload_file(self, file: bytes, s3_image_path: str):\n    return storage_service.upload_file(file, s3_image_path)\n```\n\n#### Get metadata\n\nTo get metadata for a file stored in S3:\n\n```python\nfrom config.storage import storage_service\n\ndef get_metadata(self, s3_image_path: str):\n    return storage_service.get_metadata(s3_image_path)\n```\n\n#### Change Content Type\n\nTo modify the content type of a file in S3:\n\n```python\nfrom config.storage import storage_service\ndef change_content_type(self, s3_image_path: str, content_type: str):\n    return storage_service.change_content_type(s3_image_path, content_type)\n```\n\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "fastapi_storage_helper", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "fastapi_storage_helper.StorageService", "xref": {"fqname": "fastapi_storage_helper.storage.StorageService", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "fastapi_storage_helper.storage", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "fastapi_storage_helper.storage.StorageService", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "fastapi_storage_helper.storage.StorageService.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "access_key_id", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "secret_key", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "region_name", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "bucket", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "fastapi_storage_helper.storage.StorageService.create_upload_presign_url", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "key", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "content_length", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.